msgid "3D lights and shadows"
msgstr "Soilse agus scáthanna 3D"

msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "Réamhrá"

msgid ""
"Light sources emit light that mixes with the materials and produces a "
"visible result. Light can come from several types of sources in a scene:"
msgstr ""
"Astaíonn foinsí solais solas a mheascann leis na hábhair agus a tháirgeann "
"toradh infheicthe. Is féidir solas teacht ó roinnt cineálacha foinsí i "
"radharc:"

msgid ""
"From the material itself, in the form of the emission color (though it does "
"not affect nearby objects unless baked or screen-space indirect lighting is "
"enabled)."
msgstr ""
"Ón ábhar féin, i bhfoirm an dath astaíochta (cé nach ndéanann sé difear do "
"rudaí in aice láimhe mura gcumasaítear soilsiú indíreach bácáilte nó spáis "
"scáileáin)."

msgid "Light nodes: DirectionalLight3D, OmniLight3D and SpotLight3D."
msgstr "Nóid solais: DirectionalLight3D, OmniLight3D agus Spotlight3D."

msgid ""
"Ambient light in the :ref:`Environment <class_Environment>` or :ref:"
"`doc_reflection_probes`."
msgstr ""
"Solas comhthimpeallach sa :ref:`Timpeallacht <class_Environment>` nó :ref:"
"`doc_reflection_probes`."

msgid ""
"Global illumination (:ref:`LightmapGI <doc_using_lightmap_gi>`, :ref:"
"`VoxelGI <doc_using_voxel_gi>` or :ref:`SDFGI <doc_using_sdfgi>`)."
msgstr ""
"Soilsiú domhanda (:ref:`LightmapGI <doc_using_lightmap_gi>`, :ref:`VoxelGI "
"<doc_using_voxel_gi>` nó :ref:`SDFGI <doc_using_sdfgi>`)."

msgid ""
"The emission color is a material property. You can read more about it in "
"the :ref:`doc_standard_material_3d` tutorial."
msgstr ""
"Is maoin ábhartha é an dath astaíochta. Is féidir leat tuilleadh a léamh "
"faoi sa rang teagaisc: ref: `doc_standard_material_3d`."

msgid ""
"You can compare various types of lights in action using the `3D Lights and "
"Shadows demo project <https://github.com/godotengine/godot-demo-projects/"
"tree/master/3d/lights_and_shadows>`__."
msgstr ""
"Is féidir leat cineálacha éagsúla soilse i ngníomh a chur i gcomparáid leis "
"an tionscadal taispeána `3D Lights and Shadows <https://github.com/"
"godotengine/godot-demo-projects/tree/master/3d/lights_and_shadows>`__."

msgid "Light nodes"
msgstr "Nóid éadrom"

msgid ""
"There are three types of light nodes: :ref:`class_DirectionalLight3D`, :ref:"
"`class_OmniLight3D` and :ref:`class_SpotLight3D`. Let's take a look at the "
"common parameters for lights:"
msgstr ""
"Tá trí chineál nóid solais ann: :ref: `Class_DirectionalLight3D`, :ref: "
"`Class_OmniLight3D` agus:ref: `Class_Spotlight3D`. Breathnaímid ar na "
"paraiméadair choitianta do shoilse:"

msgid "Each property has a specific function:"
msgstr "Tá feidhm shonrach ag gach maoin:"

msgid "**Color:** Base color for emitted light."
msgstr "** Dath: ** Dath bonn le haghaidh solais astaithe."

msgid ""
"**Energy:** Energy multiplier. This is useful for saturating lights or "
"working with :ref:`doc_high_dynamic_range`."
msgstr ""
"**Fuinneamh: ** Iolraitheoir fuinnimh. Tá sé seo úsáideach chun soilse a "
"sháithiú nó chun oibriú le:ref: `doc_high_dynamic_range`."

msgid ""
"**Indirect Energy:** Secondary multiplier used with indirect light (light "
"bounces). This works with :ref:`doc_using_lightmap_gi`, VoxelGI or SDFGI."
msgstr ""
"** Fuinneamh Indíreach: ** Iolraitheoir tánaisteach a úsáidtear le solas "
"indíreach (preabhálacha solais). Oibríonn sé seo le:ref: "
"`doc_using_lightmap_gi`, VoxElGI nó SDFGI."

msgid ""
"**Volumetric Fog Energy:** Secondary multiplier used with volumetric fog. "
"This only has an effect when volumetric fog is enabled."
msgstr ""
"**Fuinneamh Ceo toirtmhéadrach:** Iolraitheoir tánaisteach a úsáidtear le "
"ceo toirtmhéadrach. Níl éifeacht aige seo ach amháin nuair a bhíonn ceo "
"toirtmhéadrach cumasaithe."

msgid ""
"**Negative:** Light becomes subtractive instead of additive. It's sometimes "
"useful to manually compensate some dark corners."
msgstr ""
"**Diúltach:** Éiríonn solas dealaitheach in ionad breiseán. Tá sé úsáideach "
"uaireanta roinnt coirnéil dorcha a chúiteamh de láimh."

msgid ""
"**Specular:** Affects the intensity of the specular blob in objects affected "
"by this light. At zero, this light becomes a pure diffuse light."
msgstr ""
"**Speicular: ** Bíonn tionchar acu ar dhéine an blob speisialach i rudaí a "
"bhíonn tionchar ag an solas seo orthu. Ag nialas, éiríonn an solas seo ina "
"solas scaipthe íon."

msgid ""
"**Bake Mode:** Sets the bake mode for the light. See :ref:"
"`doc_using_lightmap_gi`."
msgstr ""
"**Mód Bácáil: ** Socraíonn sé an modh bácála don solas. Féach: ref: "
"`doc_using_lightmap_gi`."

msgid ""
"**Cull Mask:** Objects that are in the selected layers below will be "
"affected by this light. Note that objects disabled via this cull mask will "
"still cast shadows. If you don't want disabled objects to cast shadows, "
"adjust the **Cast Shadow** property on the GeometryInstance3D to the desired "
"value."
msgstr ""
"**Masc Cull: ** Beidh tionchar ag an solas seo ar rudaí atá sna sraitheanna "
"roghnaithe thíos. Tabhair faoi deara go gcaithfidh rudaí atá díchumasaithe "
"tríd an masc caill seo scáthanna Mura dteastaíonn uait go gcaitheann rudaí "
"faoi mhíchumas scáthanna, coigeartaigh an maoin **Cast Scadow** ar an "
"GeometryInstance3D go dtí an luach atá ag teastáil."

msgid ""
"See :ref:`doc_physical_light_and_camera_units` if you wish to use real world "
"units to configure your lights' intensity and color temperature."
msgstr ""
"Féach:ref: `doc_physical_light_and_camera_units` más mian leat aonaid an "
"domhain fíor a úsáid chun déine agus teocht dath do shoilse a chumrú."

msgid "Light number limits"
msgstr "Teorainneacha líon solais"

msgid ""
"When using the Forward Mobile renderer, there is a limitation of 8 "
"OmniLights + 8 SpotLights per mesh resource. There is also a limit of 256 "
"OmniLights + 256 SpotLights that can be rendered in the current camera view. "
"These limits currently cannot be changed."
msgstr ""
"Agus an renderer Forward Mobile á úsáid agat, tá teorannú ar 8 OmniLights + "
"8 SpotLights in aghaidh an acmhainne mogalra. Tá teorainn de 256 OmniLights "
"+ 256 SpotLights ann freisin ar féidir a léiriú i radharc reatha an "
"cheamara. Ní féidir na teorainneacha seo a athrú faoi láthair."

msgid ""
"With all rendering methods, up to 8 DirectionalLights can be visible at a "
"time. However, each additional DirectionalLight with shadows enabled will "
"reduce the effective shadow resolution of each DirectionalLight. This is "
"because directional shadow atlas is shared between all lights."
msgstr ""
"Le gach modh rindreála, is féidir suas le 8 DirectionAllights a bheith le "
"feiceáil ag an am. Mar sin féin, laghdóidh gach DirectionalLight breise le "
"scáthanna cumasaithe réiteach scáth éifeachtach gach DirectionalLight. Tá sé "
"seo toisc go bhfuil atlas scáth treorach roinnte idir gach soilse."

msgid ""
"If the rendering limit is exceeded, lights will start popping in and out "
"during camera movement, which can be distracting. Enabling **Distance Fade** "
"on light nodes can help reduce this issue while also improving performance. "
"Splitting your meshes into smaller portions can also help, especially for "
"level geometry (which also improves culling efficiency)."
msgstr ""
"Má sháraítear an teorainn rindreála, tosóidh soilse ag preabadh isteach agus "
"amach le linn gluaiseacht an cheamara, rud a d’fhéadfadh a bheith ag cur as "
"do dhaoine. Is féidir an cheist seo a laghdú agus feidhmíocht a fheabhsú ag "
"an am céanna má chuirtear **Fad-Chéim ** ar nóid solais ar fáil. Is féidir "
"cabhrú freisin le do chuid mogaill a roinnt ina gcodanna níos lú, go "
"háirithe maidir le céimseata leibhéal (rud a fheabhsaíonn éifeachtacht an "
"maraithe freisin)."

msgid ""
"If you need to render more lights than possible in a given rendering "
"backend, consider using :ref:`baked lightmaps <doc_using_lightmap_gi>` with "
"lights' bake mode set to **Static**. This allows lights to be fully baked, "
"which also makes them much faster to render. You can also use emissive "
"materials with any :ref:`global illumination "
"<doc_introduction_to_global_illumination>` technique as a replacement for "
"light nodes that emit light over a large area."
msgstr ""
"Más gá duit níos mó soilse a sholáthar ná mar is féidir in inneall rindreála "
"ar leith, smaoinigh ar :ref:`bácáilte lightmaps <doc_using_lightmap_gi>` le "
"soilse' mód bácála socraithe go **Statach**. Ligeann sé seo soilse a bhácáil "
"go hiomlán, rud a fhágann go bhfuil siad i bhfad níos tapúla le rindreáil. "
"Is féidir leat ábhair emissive a úsáid freisin le haon teicníc :ref:`soilsiú "
"domhanda <doc_introduction_to_global_illumination>` mar ionadach do nóid "
"solais a scaoileann solas thar limistéar mór."

msgid "Shadow mapping"
msgstr "Mapáil scáth"

msgid ""
"Lights can optionally cast shadows. This gives them greater realism (light "
"does not reach occluded areas), but it can incur a bigger performance cost. "
"There is a list of generic shadow parameters, each also has a specific "
"function:"
msgstr ""
"Is féidir le soilse scátháin a chaitheamh go roghnach Tugann sé seo "
"réalaíocht níos mó dóibh (ní shroicheann solas limistéir dhíobhálacha), ach "
"féadann costas feidhmíochta níos mó a bheith aige. Tá liosta de "
"pharaiméadair scáth cineálacha ann, tá feidhm shonrach ag gach ceann acu "
"freisin:"

msgid "**Enabled:** Check to enable shadow mapping in this light."
msgstr "**Cumasaithe: ** Seiceáil chun scáth-mapáil a chumasú sa solas seo."

msgid ""
"**Opacity:** Areas occluded are darkened by this opacity factor. Shadows are "
"fully opaque by default, but this can be changed to make shadows translucent "
"for a given light."
msgstr ""
"**Teimhneacht:** Déanann an fachtóir teimhneachta seo na limistéir atá "
"folaithe a dhorchadas. Tá scáthanna go hiomlán teimhneach de réir "
"réamhshocraithe, ach is féidir é seo a athrú chun scáthanna a dhéanamh "
"tréshoilseach do sholas ar leith."

msgid ""
"**Bias:** When this parameter is too low, self-shadowing occurs. When too "
"high, shadows separate from the casters. Tweak to what works best for you."
msgstr ""
"**Claontacht: ** Nuair a bhíonn an paraiméadar seo ró-íseal, tarlaíonn féin-"
"scáthú. Nuair a bhíonn siad ró-ard, bíonn scáthanna ar scaradh ó na casters. "
"Teach ar an méid is fearr a oibríonn duitse."

msgid ""
"**Normal Bias:** When this parameter is too low, self-shadowing occurs. When "
"too high, shadows appear misaligned from the casters. Tweak to what works "
"best for you."
msgstr ""
"** Gnáthchlaonadh: ** Nuair a bhíonn an paraiméadar seo ró-íseal, tarlaíonn "
"féin-scáthú. Nuair atá ró-ard, is cosúil go bhfuil scáthanna mí-ailínithe ó "
"na casters. Teach ar an méid is fearr a oibríonn duitse."

msgid ""
"**Transmittance Bias:** When this parameter is too low, self-shadowing "
"occurs on materials that have transmittance enabled. When too high, shadows "
"will not affect materials that have transmittance enabled consistently. "
"Tweak to what works best for you."
msgstr ""
"** Claonadh tarchurtha: ** Nuair a bhíonn an paraiméadar seo ró-íseal, "
"tarlaíonn féin-scáthú ar ábhair a bhfuil tarchuradóireacht cumasaithe acu. "
"Nuair a bhíonn siad ró-ard, ní bheidh tionchar ag scáthanna ar ábhair a "
"bhfuil tarchuradóireacht cumasaithe go comh Teach ar an méid is fearr a "
"oibríonn duitse."

msgid ""
"**Reverse Cull Face:** Some scenes work better when shadow mapping is "
"rendered with face-culling inverted."
msgstr ""
"**Aghaidh Leatha Droim ar Ais:** Feidhmíonn roinnt radharc níos fearr nuair "
"a dhéantar léarscáiliú scátha le haghaidh maraithe inbhéartaithe."

msgid ""
"**Blur:** Multiplies the shadow blur radius for this light. This works with "
"both traditional shadow mapping and contact-hardening shadows (lights with "
"**Angular Distance** or **Size** greater than ``0.0``). Higher values result "
"in softer shadows, which will also appear to be more temporally stable for "
"moving objects. The downside of increasing shadow blur is that it will make "
"the grainy pattern used for filtering more noticeable. See also :ref:"
"`doc_lights_and_shadows_shadow_filter_mode`."
msgstr ""
"**Doiléir: ** Iolraíonn sé an raidise doiléir scáth don solas seo. Oibríonn "
"sé seo le mapáil scáth traidisiúnta agus scáthanna cruithe teagmhála araon "
"(soilse len**Fad Uilleach** nó **Méid** níos mó ná ``0.0``). Bíonn scáthanna "
"níos boige mar thoradh ar luachanna níos airde, rud a bheidh cosúil go "
"bhfuil sé níos cobhsaí ó thaobh ama le haghaidh rudaí Is é an míbhuntáiste a "
"bhaineann le doiléir scáth a mhéadú ná go ndéanfaidh sé an patrún gránach a "
"úsáidtear chun scagadh níos suntasaí. Féach freis:ref: "
"`doc_lights_and_shadows_shadow_filter_mode`."

msgid "Tweaking shadow bias"
msgstr "Claontacht scáth a athrú"

msgid ""
"Below is an image of what tweaking bias looks like. Default values work for "
"most cases, but in general, it depends on the size and complexity of "
"geometry."
msgstr ""
"Anseo thíos tá íomhá de cad is cosúil le claonadh tweaking. Oibríonn "
"luachanna réamhshocraithe i bhformhór na gcásanna, ach go ginearálta, "
"braitheann sé ar mhéid agus ar chastacht na céimseata."

msgid ""
"If the **Shadow Bias** or **Shadow Normal Bias** is set too low for a given "
"light, the shadow will be \"smeared\" onto the objects. This will cause the "
"light's intended appearance to darken, and is called *shadow acne*:"
msgstr ""
"Má shocraítear an **Clacht Scáth** nó**Gnáthchlaocht Scáth** ró-íseal le "
"haghaidh solas ar leith, déanfar an scáth “smeartha” ar na rudaí. Cuirfidh "
"sé seo faoi deara cuma beartaithe an tsolais, agus tugtar air*scáth acne* "
"air:"

msgid ""
"On the other hand, if the **Shadow Bias** or **Shadow Normal Bias** is set "
"too high for a given light, the shadow may appear to be disconnected from "
"the object. This is called *peter-panning*:"
msgstr ""
"Ar an láimh eile, má tá an **Clacht Scáth** nó **Claonadh Gnáth Scáth** "
"socraithe ró-ard le haghaidh solas ar leith, b'fhéidir go bhfuil an scáth "
"dícheangailte ón réad. Tugtar uir* peter-panning* air seo:"

msgid ""
"In general, increasing **Shadow Normal Bias** is preferred over increasing "
"**Shadow Bias**. Increasing **Shadow Normal Bias** does not cause as much "
"peter-panning as increasing **Shadow Bias**, but it can still resolve most "
"shadow acne issues efficiently. The downside of increasing **Shadow Normal "
"Bias** is that it can make shadows appear thinner for certain objects."
msgstr ""
"Go ginearálta, is fearr **Gnáthchlaofacht Scáthla\" a mhéadú seachas "
"**Laofacht Scáthlaofachta** a mhéadú. Má mhéadaítear **Gnáthchlaonadh "
"Scáthaigh**, ní bheidh sé ina chúis le méadú ar **Scáth-laofacht**, ach is "
"féidir leis an chuid is mó de na saincheisteanna scáth-acainníocha a "
"réiteach go héifeachtach. Is é an míbhuntáiste a bhaineann le "
"**Gnáthchlaonadh Scáthaigh** a mhéadú ná gur féidir leis scáthanna a "
"dhéanamh níos tanaí le haghaidh rudaí áirithe."

msgid ""
"Any sort of bias issues can be fixed by :ref:`increasing the shadow map "
"resolution <doc_lights_and_shadows_balancing_performance_and_quality>`, at "
"the cost of decreased performance."
msgstr ""
"Is féidir aon sórt saincheisteanna claonta a shocrú trí :ref:`taifeach na "
"scáthléarscáile a mhéadú "
"<doc_lights_and_shadows_balancing_performance_and_quality>`, ar chostas "
"feidhmíochta laghdaithe."

msgid ""
"Tweaking shadow mapping settings is an art – there are no \"one size fits "
"all\" settings. To achieve the best visuals, you may need to use different "
"shadow bias values on a per-light basis."
msgstr ""
"Is ealaín é socruithe mapála scáth a athrú - níl aon socruithe “méid amháin "
"oireann do gach duine” ann. Chun na radhairc is fearr a bhaint amach, "
"b'fhéidir go mbeidh ort luachanna claonta scáth éagsúla a úsáid ar bhonn in "
"aghaidh an solais."

msgid ""
"**Note on Appearance Changes**: When enabling shadows on a light, be aware "
"that the light's appearance might change compared to when it's rendered "
"without shadows in the compatibility renderer. Due to limitations with older "
"mobile devices, shadows are implemented using a multi-pass rendering "
"approach so lights with shadows are rendered in sRGB space instead of linear "
"space. This change in rendering space can sometimes drastically alter the "
"light's appearance. To achieve a similar appearance to an unshadowed light, "
"you may need to adjust the light's energy setting."
msgstr ""
"**Nóta ar Athruithe Dealrama**: Agus scáthanna á chumasú ar sholas, bí ar an "
"eolas go bhféadfadh cuma an tsolais athrú i gcomparáid le nuair a dhéantar é "
"a léiriú gan scáthanna sa léiritheoir comhoiriúnachta. Mar gheall ar "
"theorainneacha le gléasanna soghluaiste níos sine, cuirtear scáthanna i "
"bhfeidhm ag baint úsáide as cur chuige rindreála ilphas ionas go ndéantar "
"soilse le scáthanna a léiriú i spás Uaireanta is féidir leis an athrú seo ar "
"an spás rindreála cuma an tsolais a athrú go suntasach. Chun cuma cosúil le "
"solas gan scáthú a bhaint amach, b'fhéidir go mbeidh ort socrú fuinnimh an "
"tsolais a choigeartú."

msgid "Directional light"
msgstr "Solas treorach"

msgid ""
"This is the most common type of light and represents a light source very far "
"away (such as the sun). It is also the cheapest light to compute and should "
"be used whenever possible (although it's not the cheapest shadow-map to "
"compute, but more on that later)."
msgstr ""
"Is é seo an cineál solais is coitianta agus léiríonn sé foinse solais an-"
"fhada ar shiúl (mar shampla an ghrian). Is é an solas is saoire é freisin le "
"ríomh agus ba chóir é a úsáid nuair is féidir (cé nach é an léarscáil scáth "
"is saoire é le ríomh, ach níos mó faoi sin níos déanaí)."

msgid ""
"Directional light models an infinite number of parallel light rays covering "
"the whole scene. The directional light node is represented by a big arrow "
"which indicates the direction of the light rays. However, the position of "
"the node does not affect the lighting at all and can be anywhere."
msgstr ""
"Samhlaíonn solas treorach líon gan teorainn gathanna solais comhthreomhara a "
"chlúdaíonn an radharc iomlán Léiríonn saighead mór an nód solais treorach a "
"léiríonn treo na ngathanna solais. Mar sin féin, ní dhéanann suíomh an nód "
"difear don soilsiú ar chor ar bith agus féadann sé a bheith in áit ar bith."

msgid ""
"Every face whose front-side is hit by the light rays is lit, while the "
"others stay dark. Unlike most other light types, directional lights don't "
"have specific parameters."
msgstr ""
"Tá gach aghaidh a bhfuil a thaobh tosaigh buailte ag na gathanna solais ar "
"lasadh, agus fanann na cinn eile dorcha. Murab ionann agus an chuid is mó de "
"na cineálacha solais eile, níl paraiméadair shonracha ag soilse treorach."

msgid ""
"The directional light also offers a **Angular Distance** property, which "
"determines the light's angular size in degrees. Increasing this above "
"``0.0`` will make shadows softer at greater distances from the caster, while "
"also affecting the sun's appearance in procedural sky materials. This is "
"called a *contact-hardening* shadow (also known as PCSS)."
msgstr ""
"Cuireann an solas treorach maoin **Fad Uilleach** ar fáil freisin, a "
"chinneann méid uilleach an tsolais i gcéimeanna. Má mhéadaítear é seo os "
"cionn ``0.0``, beidh scáthanna níos boige ag achair níos mó ón gcástálaí, "
"agus beidh tionchar acu freisin ar chuma na gréine in ábhair spéir nós "
"imeachta. Tugtar scáth*teagmhála-cruaíochta* air seo (ar a dtugtar PCSS "
"freisin)."

msgid ""
"For reference, the angular distance of the Sun viewed from the Earth is "
"approximately ``0.5``. This kind of shadow is expensive, so check the "
"recommendations in :ref:`doc_lights_and_shadows_pcss_recommendations` if "
"setting this value above ``0.0`` on lights with shadows enabled."
msgstr ""
"Mar thagairt, is é fad uilleach na Gréine a bhreathnaítear ón Domhan thart "
"ar ``0.5``. Tá scáth den chineál seo daor, mar sin seiceáil na moltaí in:"
"ref: `doc_lights_and_shadows_pcss_recomations` má shocraíonn an luach seo os "
"cionn ``0.0`` ar shoilse le scáthanna cumasaithe."

msgid "Directional shadow mapping"
msgstr "Mapáil scáth treorach"

msgid ""
"To compute shadow maps, the scene is rendered (only depth) from an "
"orthogonal point of view that covers the whole scene (or up to the max "
"distance). There is, however, a problem with this approach because objects "
"closer to the camera receive low-resolution shadows that may appear blocky."
msgstr ""
"Chun scáthléarscáileanna a ríomh, déantar an radharc a léiriú (doimhneacht "
"amháin) ó thaobh orthogonal a chlúdaíonn an radharc iomlán (nó suas go dtí "
"an fad uasta). Tá fadhb leis an gcur chuige seo, áfach, toisc go bhfaigheann "
"rudaí níos gaire don cheamara scáthanna taifigh íseal a d'fhéadfadh a bheith "
"cosúil go bhfuil siad blocach."

msgid ""
"To fix this, a technique named *Parallel Split Shadow Maps* (PSSM) is used. "
"This splits the view frustum in 2 or 4 areas. Each area gets its own shadow "
"map. This allows small areas close to the viewer to have the same shadow "
"resolution as a huge, far-away area. When shadows are enabled for "
"DirectionalLight3D, the default shadow mode is PSSM with 4 splits. In "
"scenarios where an object is large enough to appear in all four splits, it "
"results in increased draw calls. Specifically, such an object will be "
"rendered five times in total: once for each of the four shadow splits and "
"once for the final scene rendering. This can impact performance, "
"understanding this behavior is important for optimizing your scene and "
"managing performance expectations."
msgstr ""
"Chun é seo a réiteach, úsáidtear teicníc darb ainm *Scáthléarscáileanna "
"Roinnte Comhthreomhara* (PSSM). Roinneann sé seo an frustum radhairc i 2 nó "
"4 limistéar. Faigheann gach ceantar a scáthléarscáil féin. Ligeann sé seo do "
"limistéir bheaga atá gar don bhreathnóir an scáth-thaifeach céanna a bheith "
"acu agus limistéar ollmhór i bhfad uaidh. Nuair atá scáthanna cumasaithe le "
"haghaidh DirectionalLight3D, is é PSSM an modh scáth réamhshocraithe le 4 "
"scoilt. I gcásanna ina bhfuil réad mór go leor le feiceáil i ngach ceann de "
"na ceithre scoilt, bíonn glaonna tarraingthe méadaithe mar thoradh air. Go "
"sonrach, déanfar a leithéid de réad a rindreáil cúig huaire san iomlán: uair "
"amháin do gach ceann de na ceithre scoilteadh scátha agus uair amháin le "
"haghaidh rindreála an radhairc deiridh. Is féidir leis seo tionchar a imirt "
"ar fheidhmíocht, tá sé tábhachtach an iompar seo a thuiscint chun do radharc "
"a bharrfheabhsú agus chun ionchais feidhmíochta a bhainistiú."

msgid "With this, shadows become more detailed:"
msgstr "Leis seo, éiríonn scáthanna níos mionsonraithe:"

msgid "To control PSSM, a number of parameters are exposed:"
msgstr "Chun PSSM a rialú, nochtar roinnt paraiméadair:"

msgid ""
"Each split distance is controlled relative to the camera far (or shadow "
"**Max Distance** if greater than ``0.0``). ``0.0`` is the eye position and "
"``1.0`` is where the shadow ends at a distance. Splits are in-between. "
"Default values generally work well, but tweaking the first split a bit is "
"common to give more detail to close objects (like a character in a third-"
"person game)."
msgstr ""
"Rialaítear gach achar scoilte i gcoibhneas leis an gceamara i bhfad (nó "
"scáth** Fad Uas** má tá sé níos mó ná ``0.0``). Is é `0.0`` suíomh na súl "
"agus ``1.0`` an áit a gcríochnaíonn an scáth ar fad. Tá scoilteanna idir. De "
"ghnáth oibríonn luachanna réamhshocraithe go maith, ach is coitianta an "
"chéad scoilt a athrú beagán chun níos mó sonraí a thabhairt do rudaí dúnta "
"(cosúil le carachtar i gcluiche tríú duine)."

msgid ""
"Always make sure to set a shadow **Max Distance** according to what the "
"scene needs. A lower maximum distance will result in better-looking shadows "
"and better performance, as fewer objects will need to be included in shadow "
"rendering. You can also adjust **Fade Start** to control how aggressive the "
"shadow fade-out should be at a distance. For scenes where the **Max "
"Distance** fully covers the scene at any given camera position, you can "
"increase **Fade Start** to ``1.0`` to prevent the shadow from fading at a "
"distance. This should not be done in scenes where **Max Distance** doesn't "
"fully cover the scene, as the shadow will appear to be suddenly cut off at a "
"distance."
msgstr ""
"Déan cinnte scáth a shocrú i gcónaí** Fad Uas** de réir na rudaí a "
"theastaíonn ón radharc. Beidh scáthanna níos fearr agus feidhmíocht níos "
"fearr mar thoradh ar fad uasta níos ísle, mar ní mór níos lú rudaí a áireamh "
"i scáth-rindreáil. Is féidir leat **Fade Start** a choigeartú freisin chun a "
"rialú cé chomh ionsaitheach agus ba chóir go mbeadh an scáth fade-out i "
"gcéin. Maidir le radhairc ina gclúdaíonn an **Uastachad** an radharc go "
"hiomlán ag aon suíomh ceamara ar leith, is féidir leat **Fade Start** a "
"mhéadú go `1.0`` chun an scáth a chosc ó dhífeadh i gcéin. Níor chóir é seo "
"a dhéanamh i radhairc nach gclúdaíonn **Max Distance** an radharc go "
"hiomlán, mar is cosúil go ndéanfar an scáth a ghearradh amach go tobann ag "
"fad."

msgid ""
"Sometimes, the transition between a split and the next can look bad. To fix "
"this, the **Blend Splits** option can be turned on, which sacrifices detail "
"and performance in exchange for smoother transitions:"
msgstr ""
"Uaireanta, is féidir go mbeadh cuma dona ar an aistriú idir scoilt agus an "
"chéad cheann eile. Chun é seo a shocrú, is féidir an rogha **Blend Splits** "
"a chasadh air, a íobraíonn mionsonraí agus feidhmíocht mar mhalairt ar "
"aistrithe níos réidh:"

msgid ""
"The **Shadow > Normal Bias** parameter can be used to fix special cases of "
"self-shadowing when objects are perpendicular to the light. The only "
"downside is that it makes the shadow a bit thinner. Consider increasing "
"**Shadow > Normal Bias** before increasing **Shadow > Bias** in most "
"situations."
msgstr ""
"Is féidir an paraiméadar **Scáth > Gnáthlaofacht** a úsáid chun cásanna "
"speisialta féinscáthfhoghlaim a shocrú nuair a bhíonn rudaí ingearach leis "
"an solas. Is é an t-aon taobh thíos ná go ndéanann sé an scáth beagán níos "
"tanaí. Smaoinigh ar **Scáth > Gnáthlaofacht** a mhéadú sula méadaítear "
"**Scáth > Laofacht** i bhformhór na gcásanna."

msgid ""
"Lastly, **Pancake Size** is a property that can be adjusted to fix missing "
"shadows when using large objects with unsubdivided meshes. Only change this "
"value if you notice missing shadows that are not related to shadow biasing "
"issues."
msgstr ""
"Ar deireadh, is maoin é **Méid Pancóga** is féidir a choigeartú chun "
"scáthanna atá in easnamh a shocrú agus rudaí móra á n-úsáid acu le mogalra "
"neamhfho-roinnte. Ní athraigh an luach seo ach má thugann tú faoi deara "
"scáthanna atá in easnamh nach mbaineann le saincheisteanna claonta scáth."

msgid "Omni light"
msgstr "Solas Omni"

msgid ""
"Omni light is a point source that emits light spherically in all directions "
"up to a given radius."
msgstr ""
"Is foinse pointe é solas Omni a astaíonn solas go sféarúil i ngach treo suas "
"go raidise ar leith."

msgid ""
"In real life, light attenuation is an inverse function, which means omni "
"lights don't have a radius. This is a problem because it means computing "
"several omni lights would become demanding."
msgstr ""
"Sa saol fíor, is feidhm inbhéarach é laghdú solais, rud a chiallaíonn nach "
"bhfuil raidise ag soilse omni. Is fadhb í seo toisc go gciallaíonn sé go "
"mbeadh éileamh ar roinnt soilse omni a ríomh."

msgid ""
"To solve this, a **Range** parameter is introduced together with an "
"attenuation function."
msgstr ""
"Chun é seo a réiteach, tugtar paraiméadar **Raon** isteach in éineacht le "
"feidhm laghdaithe."

msgid ""
"These two parameters allow tweaking how this works visually in order to find "
"aesthetically pleasing results."
msgstr ""
"Ligeann an dá pharaiméadar seo athrú a dhéanamh ar an gcaoi a n-oibríonn sé "
"seo chun torthaí taitneamhach ó thaobh na haeistéitiúla a fháil."

msgid ""
"A **Size** parameter is also available in OmniLight3D. Increasing this value "
"will make the light fade out slower and shadows appear blurrier when far "
"away from the caster. This can be used to simulate area lights to an extent. "
"This is called a *contact-hardening* shadow (also known as PCSS). This kind "
"of shadow is expensive, so check the recommendations in :ref:"
"`doc_lights_and_shadows_pcss_recommendations` if setting this value above "
"``0.0`` on lights with shadows enabled."
msgstr ""
"Tá paraiméadar **Méid** ar fáil freisin in OmniLight3D. Má mhéadaítear an "
"luach seo, déanfaidh an solas dul amach níos moille agus is cosúil go bhfuil "
"scáthanna níos doiléire nuair a bhíonn siad i bhfad Is féidir é seo a úsáid "
"chun soilse limistéir a insamhail go pointe áirithe. Tugtar scáth*teagmhála-"
"cruaíochta* air seo (ar a dtugtar PCSS freisin). Tá scáth den chineál seo "
"daor, mar sin seiceáil na moltaí in:ref: "
"`doc_lights_and_shadows_pcss_recomations` má shocraíonn an luach seo os "
"cionn ``0.0`` ar shoilse le scáthanna cumasaithe."

msgid "Omni shadow mapping"
msgstr "Mapáil scáth Omni"

msgid ""
"Omni light shadow mapping is relatively straightforward. The main issue that "
"needs to be considered is the algorithm used to render it."
msgstr ""
"Tá mapáil scáth solais Omni réasúnta simplí. Is é an príomhcheist is gá a "
"mheas ná an algartam a úsáidtear chun é a rinneadh."

msgid ""
"Omni Shadows can be rendered as either **Dual Paraboloid** or **Cube** "
"mapped. **Dual Parabolid** renders quickly, but can cause deformations, "
"while **Cube** is more correct, but slower. The default is **Cube**, but "
"consider changing it to **Dual Parabolid** for lights where it doesn't make "
"much of a visual difference."
msgstr ""
"Is féidir Omni Shadows a léiriú mar **Dual Paraboloid** nó **Cube** "
"mapáilte. Déanann ** Dual Parabolid** a rinneadh go tapa, ach féadann sé "
"dífhoirmiú a bheith ina chúis le dífhoirmiú, cé go bhfuil **Cube** níos "
"ceart, ach níos moille. Is é **Cube** an réamhshocraithe, ach smaoinigh ar é "
"a athrú go **Dual Parabolid** le haghaidh soilse nuair nach ndéanann sé "
"mórán difríochta amhairc."

msgid ""
"If the objects being rendered are mostly irregular and subdivided, Dual "
"Paraboloid is usually enough. In any case, as these shadows are cached in a "
"shadow atlas (more on that at the end), it may not make a difference in "
"performance for most scenes."
msgstr ""
"Má tá na rudaí atá á rinneadh neamhrialta agus fo-roinnte den chuid is mó, "
"is gnách go leor Dual Paraboloid. Ar aon chuma, toisc go ndéantar na "
"scáthanna seo a chosc i atlas scáth (níos mó faoi sin ag an deireadh), "
"b'fhéidir nach ndéanfaidh sé difríocht i bhfeidhmíocht don chuid is mó de na "
"radhairc."

msgid ""
"Omni lights with shadows enabled can make use of projectors. The projector "
"texture will *multiply* the light's color by the color at a given point on "
"the texture. As a result, lights will usually appear to be darker once a "
"projector texture is assigned; you can increase **Energy** to compensate for "
"this."
msgstr ""
"Is féidir le soilse Omni le scáthanna cumasaithe teilgeoirí a úsáid. "
"Déanfaidh uigeacht an teilgeoir* iolraithe* dath an tsolais de réir an dath "
"ag pointe ar leith ar an uigeacht. Mar thoradh air sin, is cosúil go mbíonn "
"soilse níos dorcha de ghnáth nuair a shanntar uigeacht teilgeoir; is féidir "
"leat** Fuinneamh a mhéadú chun é seo a chúiteamh."

msgid ""
"Omni light projector textures require a special 360° panorama mapping, "
"similar to :ref:`class_PanoramaSkyMaterial` textures."
msgstr ""
"Teastaíonn uigeachtaí teilgeoir solais Omni mapáil léargais speisialta 360°, "
"cosúil le:ref: uigeachtaí `Class_PanoramaSkyMaterial`."

msgid "With the projector texture below, the following result is obtained:"
msgstr "Leis an uigeacht teilgeoir thíos, faightear an toradh seo a leanas:"

msgid ""
"If you've acquired omni projectors in the form of cubemap images, you can "
"use `this web-based conversion tool <https://danilw.github.io/GLSL-howto/"
"cubemap_to_panorama_js/cubemap_to_panorama.html>`__ to convert them to a "
"single panorama image."
msgstr ""
"Má tá omni-theilgeoirí faighte agat i bhfoirm íomhánna ciúbmap, is féidir "
"leat `__ a úsáid chun an uirlis chomhshó gréasán-bhunaithe seo a thiontú "
"<https://danilw.github.io/GLSL-howto/cubemap_to_panorama_js/"
"cubemap_to_panorama.html>`__ chuig íomhá lánléargais amháin."

msgid "Spot light"
msgstr "Solas spota"

msgid ""
"Spot lights are similar to omni lights, except they emit light only into a "
"cone (or \"cutoff\"). They are useful to simulate flashlights, car lights, "
"reflectors, spots, etc. This type of light is also attenuated towards the "
"opposite direction it points to."
msgstr ""
"Tá soilse spota cosúil le soilse omni, ach amháin nach n-astaíonn siad solas "
"ach isteach i gcóin (nó “gearradh”). Tá siad úsáideach chun soilse lasc, "
"soilse gluaisteán, frithchaiteoirí, spotaí, srl a insamhail Déantar an "
"cineál solais seo a laghdú freisin i dtreo an treo eile a thugann sé in iúl."

msgid ""
"Spot lights share the same **Range**, **Attenuation** and **Size** as "
"OmniLight3D, and add two extra parameters:"
msgstr ""
"Roinneann spota soilse an chéann**Raon**, **Laistiú** agus **Méid** mar "
"OmniLight3D, agus cuir dhá pharaiméadar breise leis:"

msgid "**Angle:** The aperture angle of the light."
msgstr "** Uillinn: ** Uillinn cúlra an tsolais."

msgid ""
"**Angle Attenuation:** The cone attenuation, which helps soften the cone "
"borders."
msgstr ""
"** Laghdú Uillinn: ** An laghdú cón, a chuidíonn le teorainneacha na gcóin a "
"mhaolú."

msgid "Spot shadow mapping"
msgstr "Mapáil scáth spota"

msgid ""
"Spots feature the same parameters as omni lights for shadow mapping. "
"Rendering spot shadow maps is significantly faster compared to omni lights, "
"as only one shadow texture needs to be rendered (instead of rendering 6 "
"faces, or 2 in dual parabolid mode)."
msgstr ""
"Tá na paraiméadair chéanna ag spotaí le soilse omni le haghaidh mapáil "
"scáth. Tá léarscáileanna scáth spota a rindreáil i bhfad níos gasta i "
"gcomparáid le soilse omni, toisc nach gá ach uigeacht scáth amháin a léiriú "
"(in ionad 6 aghaidh a rindreáil, nó 2 i mód dé-pharabolid)."

msgid ""
"Spot lights with shadows enabled can make use of projectors. The projector "
"texture will *multiply* the light's color by the color at a given point on "
"the texture. As a result, lights will usually appear to be darker once a "
"projector texture is assigned; you can increase **Energy** to compensate for "
"this."
msgstr ""
"Is féidir le spota soilse le scáthanna cumasaithe teilgeoirí a úsáid. "
"Déanfaidh uigeacht an teilgeoir* iolraithe* dath an tsolais de réir an dath "
"ag pointe ar leith ar an uigeacht. Mar thoradh air sin, is cosúil go mbíonn "
"soilse níos dorcha de ghnáth nuair a shanntar uigeacht teilgeoir; is féidir "
"leat** Fuinneamh a mhéadú chun é seo a chúiteamh."

msgid ""
"Unlike omni light projectors, a spot light projector texture doesn't need to "
"follow a special format to look correct. It will be mapped in a way similar "
"to a :ref:`decal <doc_using_decals>`."
msgstr ""
"Murab ionann agus teilgeoirí solais omni, ní gá d'uigeacht spotteilgeoir "
"solais formáid speisialta a leanúint chun breathnú ceart. Déanfar é a "
"mhapáil ar bhealach cosúil le :ref:`decal <doc_using_decals>`."

msgid ""
"Spot lights with wide angles will have lower-quality shadows than spot "
"lights with narrow angles, as the shadow map is spread over a larger "
"surface. At angles wider than 89 degrees, spot light shadows will stop "
"working entirely. If you need shadows for wider lights, use an omni light "
"instead."
msgstr ""
"Beidh scáthanna ar chaighdeán níos ísle ag spota soilse le huillinneacha "
"leathana ná spota soilse le huillinneacha caol, de réir mar a scaiptear an "
"léarscáil scáth Ag uillinneacha níos leithne ná 89 céim, stop scáthanna "
"solais spota ag obair go hiomlán. Má theastaíonn scáthanna uait le haghaidh "
"soilse níos leithne, bain úsáid as solas omni ina ionad sin."

msgid "Shadow atlas"
msgstr "Atlas scáth"

msgid ""
"Unlike Directional lights, which have their own shadow texture, omni and "
"spot lights are assigned to slots of a shadow atlas. This atlas can be "
"configured in the advanced Project Settings (**Rendering > Lights And "
"Shadows > Positional Shadow**)."
msgstr ""
"Murab ionann agus soilse Treo, a bhfuil a n-uigeacht scáth féin acu, sanntar "
"soilse omni agus spotsoilse do shliotáin d’atlas scáth. Is féidir an t-atlas "
"seo a chumrú sna hardsocruithe Tionscadail (** Rindreáil > Soilse Agus "
"Scáthanna > Scáth Dearfach**)."

msgid ""
"The resolution applies to the whole shadow atlas. This atlas is divided into "
"four quadrants:"
msgstr ""
"Baineann an rún leis an atlas scáth iomlán. Tá an atlas seo roinnte ina "
"cheithre cheathrar cearnach:"

msgid ""
"Each quadrant can be subdivided to allocate any number of shadow maps; the "
"following is the default subdivision:"
msgstr ""
"Is féidir gach cearnán a fho-roinnt chun aon líon scáthléarscáileanna a "
"leithdháileadh; is é seo a leanas an fho-rannán réamhshocraithe:"

msgid "The shadow atlas allocates space as follows:"
msgstr "Leithdháileann an atlas scáth spás mar seo a leanas:"

msgid ""
"The biggest shadow map size (when no subdivision is used) represents a light "
"the size of the screen (or bigger)."
msgstr ""
"Léiríonn méid an scáth léarscáileáin is mó (nuair nach n-úsáidtear aon fho-"
"rannán) solas méid an scáileáin (nó níos mó)."

msgid ""
"Subdivisions (smaller maps) represent shadows for lights that are further "
"away from view and proportionally smaller."
msgstr ""
"Léiríonn fo-alt (léarscáileanna níos lú) scáthanna do shoilse atá níos faide "
"ón radharc agus níos lú go comhréireach."

msgid "Every frame, the following procedure is performed for all lights:"
msgstr "Gach fráma, déantar an nós imeachta seo a leanas do gach soilse:"

msgid ""
"Check if the light is on a slot of the right size. If not, re-render it and "
"move it to a larger/smaller slot."
msgstr ""
"Seiceáil an bhfuil an solas ar sliotán den mhéid ceart. Mura bhfuil, déan é "
"a athghabháil agus bog chuig sliotán níos móra/níos lú é."

msgid ""
"Check if any object affecting the shadow map has changed. If it did, re-"
"render the light."
msgstr ""
"Seiceáil an bhfuil athrú tagtha ar aon rud a théann i bhfeidhm ar an scáth- "
"Má rinne sé, déan an solas a athsholáthar."

msgid ""
"If neither of the above has happened, nothing is done, and the shadow is "
"left untouched."
msgstr ""
"Mura tharla ceachtar díobh thuas, ní dhéantar aon rud, agus fágtar an scáth "
"gan teagmháil."

msgid ""
"If the slots in a quadrant are full, lights are pushed back to smaller "
"slots, depending on size and distance. If all slots in all quadrants are "
"full, some lights will not be able to render shadows even if shadows are "
"enabled on them."
msgstr ""
"Má tá na sliotáin i gcearnán lán, brúitear soilse ar ais chuig sliotáin níos "
"lú, ag brath ar mhéid agus achar. Má tá gach sliotán i ngach cearnach lán, "
"ní bheidh roinnt soilse in ann scáthanna a léiriú fiú má tá scáthanna "
"cumasaithe orthu."

msgid ""
"The default shadow allocation strategy allows rendering up to 88 lights with "
"shadows enabled in the camera frustum (4 + 4 + 16 + 64):"
msgstr ""
"Ligeann an straitéis leithdháilte scáth réamhshocraithe suas le 88 soilse a "
"rindreáil le scáthanna cumasaithe sa cheamara frustum (4 + 4 + 16 + 64):"

msgid "The first and most detailed quadrant can store 4 shadows."
msgstr "Is féidir leis an gcéad cheathrant is mionsonraithe 4 scáth a stóráil."

msgid "The second quadrant can store 4 other shadows."
msgstr "Is féidir leis an dara ceadrant 4 scáth eile a stóráil."

msgid "The third quadrant can store 16 shadows, with less detail."
msgstr ""
"Is féidir leis an tríú ceadrant 16 scáth a stóráil, le níos lú mionsonraí."

msgid ""
"The fourth and least detailed quadrant can store 64 shadows, with even less "
"detail."
msgstr ""
"Is féidir leis an gceathrú agus an ceathrú cuid is lú mionsonraithe 64 scáth "
"a stóráil, agus níos lú sonraí fós ann."

msgid ""
"Using a higher number of shadows per quadrant allows supporting a greater "
"amount of total lights with shadows enabled, while also improving "
"performance (as shadows will be rendered at a lower resolution for each "
"light). However, increasing the number of shadows per quadrant comes at the "
"cost of lower shadow quality."
msgstr ""
"Trí líon níos airde scáthanna in aghaidh an cheadrant a úsáid is féidir tacú "
"le méid níos mó soilse iomlána le scáthanna cumasaithe, agus feidhmíocht a "
"fheabhsú freisin (toisc go ndéanfar scáthanna a léiriú ag taifeach níos ísle "
"do gach solas). Mar sin féin, tagann líon na scáthanna in aghaidh an "
"cheadrant a mhéadú ar chostas cáilíochta scáth níos ísle."

msgid ""
"In some cases, you may want to use a different allocation strategy. For "
"example, in a top-down game where all lights are around the same size, you "
"may want to set all quadrants to have the same subdivision so that all "
"lights have shadows of similar quality level."
msgstr ""
"I roinnt cásanna, b'fhéidir gur mhaith leat straitéis leithdháilte difriúil "
"a úsáid. Mar shampla, i gcluiche barr anuas ina bhfuil na soilse go léir "
"timpeall an méid céanna, b'fhéidir gur mhaith leat gach cearnach a shocrú "
"chun an fo-rannán céanna a bheith acu ionas go mbeidh scáthanna de leibhéal "
"cáilíochta den chineál céanna ag gach soilse."

msgid "Balancing performance and quality"
msgstr "Cothromú feidhmíocht agus cáilíocht"

msgid ""
"Shadow rendering is a critical topic in 3D rendering performance. It's "
"important to make the right choices here to avoid creating bottlenecks."
msgstr ""
"Is ábhar criticiúil é rindreáil scáth i bhfeidhmíocht rindreála 3D. Tá sé "
"tábhachtach na roghanna cearta a dhéanamh anseo chun stragaill a chruthú a "
"sheachaint."

msgid ""
"Directional shadow quality settings can be changed at run-time by calling "
"the appropriate :ref:`class_RenderingServer` methods."
msgstr ""
"Is féidir socruithe cáilíochta scáth treorach a athrú ag am rith trí ghlaoch "
"ar na modhanna oiriúnacha: ref: `Class_RenderingServer`."

msgid ""
"Positional (omni/spot) shadow quality settings can be changed at run-time on "
"the root :ref:`class_Viewport`."
msgstr ""
"Is féidir socruithe cáilíochta scáth suímh (omni/spot) a athrú ag am rith ar "
"an bhfréamh: ref: `Class_Viewport`."

msgid "Shadow map size"
msgstr "Méid an léarscáileáin"

msgid ""
"High shadow resolutions result in sharper shadows, but at a significant "
"performance cost. It should also be noted that *sharper shadows are not "
"always more realistic*. In most cases, this should be kept at its default "
"value of ``4096`` or decreased to ``2048`` for low-end GPUs."
msgstr ""
"Bíonn scáthanna níos géire mar thoradh ar rúin ardscáth, ach ar chostas "
"feidhmíochta suntasach. Ba chóir a thabhairt faoi deara freisin nach mbíonn "
"scáthanna níos géire i gcónaí* níos réadúla. I bhformhór na gcásanna, ba "
"chóir é seo a choinneáil ag a luach réamhshocraithe de ``4096`` nó a laghdú "
"go ``2048`` do GPUanna deiridh íseal."

msgid ""
"If positional shadows become too blurry after decreasing the shadow map "
"size, you can counteract this by adjusting the :ref:`shadow atlas "
"<doc_lights_and_shadows_shadow_atlas>` quadrants to contain fewer shadows. "
"This will allow each shadow to be rendered at a higher resolution."
msgstr ""
"Má éiríonn scáthanna suímh ró-dhoiléir tar éis laghdú a dhéanamh ar mhéid na "
"scáthléarscáile, is féidir leat é seo a fhrithghníomhú tríd an :ref:`atlas "
"scáth <doc_lights_and_shadows_shadow_atlas>` a choigeartú chun níos lú "
"scáthanna a bheith ann. Tabharfaidh sé seo deis do gach scáth a rindreáil ag "
"taifeach níos airde."

msgid "Shadow filter mode"
msgstr "Modh scagaire scáth"

msgid ""
"Several shadow map quality settings can be chosen here. The default **Soft "
"Low** is a good balance between performance and quality for scenes with "
"detailed textures, as the texture detail will help make the dithering "
"pattern less noticeable."
msgstr ""
"Is féidir roinnt socruithe cáilíochta scáthléarscála a roghnú anseo. Is é an "
"réamhshocraithe**Soft Low** cothromaíocht mhaith idir feidhmíocht agus "
"cáilíocht do radhairc le uigeachtaí mionsonraithe, mar go gcabhróidh "
"mionsonraí na uigeachta leis an patrún dithering a dhéanamh chomh suntasach."

msgid ""
"However, in projects with less detailed textures, the shadow dithering "
"pattern may be more visible. To hide this pattern, you can either enable :"
"ref:`doc_3d_antialiasing_taa`, :ref:`doc_3d_antialiasing_fsr2`, :ref:"
"`doc_3d_antialiasing_fxaa`, or increase the shadow filter quality to **Soft "
"Medium** or higher."
msgstr ""
"Mar sin féin, i dtionscadail a bhfuil uigeachtaí nach bhfuil chomh "
"mionsonraithe acu, d'fhéadfadh go mbeadh an patrún dithering scáth níos Chun "
"an patrún seo a cheilt, is féidir leat:ref: `doc_3d_antialiasing_taa`, :ref: "
"`doc_3d_antialiasing_fsr2`, :ref: `doc_3d_antialiasing_fxaa` a chumasú, nó "
"cáilíocht an scáth scagaire a mhéadú go **Soft Meán** nó níos airde."

msgid ""
"The **Soft Very Low** setting will automatically decrease shadow blur to "
"make artifacts from the low sample count less visible. Conversely, the "
"**Soft High** and **Soft Ultra** settings will automatically increase shadow "
"blur to better make use of the increased sample count."
msgstr ""
"Laghdóidh an socrúit** Soft Very Low** doiléir scáth go huathoibríoch chun "
"déantáin ón líon íseal samplaí a dhéanamh chomh infheicthe. Os a choinne "
"sin, méadóidh na socruithe **Soft High** agus **Soft Ultra** doiléir scáth "
"go huathoibríoch chun úsáid níos fearr a bhaint as an líon samplaí méadaithe."

msgid "16-bits versus 32-bit"
msgstr "16-giotán i gcoinne 32-giotán"

msgid ""
"By default, Godot uses 16-bit depth textures for shadow map rendering. This "
"is recommended in most cases as it performs better without a noticeable "
"difference in quality."
msgstr ""
"De réir réamhshocraithe, úsáideann Godot uigeachtaí doimhneachta 16-giotán "
"le haghaidh rindreáil léarscá Moltar é seo i bhformhór na gcásanna mar go "
"bhfeidhmíonn sé níos fearr gan difríocht suntasach i gcáilíocht."

msgid ""
"If **16 Bits** is disabled, 32-bit depth textures will be used instead. This "
"can result in less artifacting in large scenes and large lights with shadows "
"enabled. However, the difference is often barely visible, yet this can have "
"a significant performance cost."
msgstr ""
"Má tá **16 Giotán** díchumasaithe, úsáidfear uigeachtaí doimhneachta 32-"
"giotán ina ionad sin. D'fhéadfadh sé seo a bheith mar thoradh ar níos lú "
"déantán i radhairc mhóra agus soilse móra le scáthanna cumasaithe. Mar sin "
"féin, is ar éigean go bhfeictear an difríocht go minic, ach is féidir go "
"mbeadh costas feidhmíochta suntasach ag baint leis seo."

msgid "Light/shadow distance fade"
msgstr "Caitheadh achar solas/scáth"

msgid ""
"OmniLight3D and SpotLight3D offer several properties to hide distant lights. "
"This can improve performance significantly in large scenes with dozens of "
"lights or more."
msgstr ""
"Cuireann OmniLight3D agus Spotlight3D roinnt airíonna ar fáil chun soilse i "
"bhfad i gcéin a cheilt. Féadann sé seo feidhmíocht a fheabhsú go suntasach i "
"radhairc móra le mórán soilse nó níos mó."

msgid ""
"**Enabled:** Controls whether distance fade (a form of :abbr:`LOD (Level of "
"Detail)`) is enabled. The light will fade out over **Begin + Length**, after "
"which it will be culled and not sent to the shader at all. Use this to "
"reduce the number of active lights in a scene and thus improve performance."
msgstr ""
"**Cumasaithe:** Rialaíonn cé acu an bhfuil fad-chéimniú (foirm de :abbr:`LOD "
"(Leibhéal Mionsonraithe)`) cumasaithe. Scaipfidh an solas thar **Tosaigh + "
"Fad**, agus ina dhiaidh sin déanfar é a bhaint agus ní sheolfar chuig an "
"scáthlán é ar chor ar bith. Bain úsáid as seo chun líon na soilse gníomhacha "
"i radharc a laghdú agus mar sin feabhas a chur ar fheidhmíocht."

msgid ""
"**Begin:** The distance from the camera at which the light begins to fade "
"away (in 3D units)."
msgstr ""
"**Tosaigh: ** An fad ón gceamara ag a dtosaíonn an solas ag dul as imeacht "
"(in aonaid 3D)."

msgid ""
"**Shadow:** The distance from the camera at which the shadow begins to fade "
"away (in 3D units). This can be used to fade out shadows sooner compared to "
"the light, further improving performance. Only available if shadows are "
"enabled for the light."
msgstr ""
"**Scáth: ** An fad ón gceamara ag a dtosaíonn an scáth ag dul as imeacht (in "
"aonaid 3D). Is féidir é seo a úsáid chun scáthanna a shaothrú níos luaithe i "
"gcomparáid leis an solas, ag feabhsú níos mó feidhmíochta. Ar fáil ach "
"amháin má tá scáthanna cumasaithe don solas."

msgid ""
"**Length:** The distance over which the light and shadow fades (in 3D "
"units). The light becomes slowly more transparent over this distance and is "
"completely invisible at the end. Higher values result in a smoother fade-out "
"transition, which is more suited when the camera moves fast."
msgstr ""
"**Fad: ** An fad thar a dtagann an solas agus an scáth (in aonaid 3D). "
"Éiríonn an solas níos trédhearcach go mall thar an achar seo agus tá sé "
"dofheicthe go hiomlán ag an deireadh. Mar thoradh ar luachanna níos airde "
"bíonn aistriú níos réidh ag fade-out, rud atá níos oiriúnaí nuair a "
"ghluaiseann an ceamara go tapa."

msgid "PCSS recommendations"
msgstr "Moltaí PCSS"

msgid ""
"Percentage-closer soft shadows (PCSS) provide a more realistic shadow "
"mapping appearance, with the penumbra size varying depending on the distance "
"between the caster and the surface receiving the shadow. This comes at a "
"high performance cost, especially for directional lights."
msgstr ""
"Soláthraíonn scáthanna boga níos dlúithe do chéatadán (PCSS) cuma "
"léarscáileála scáth níos réalaíoch, agus méid an penumbra ag athrú ag brath "
"ar an bhfad idir an castóir agus an dromchla a fhaigheann an scáth. Tagann "
"sé seo ag costas ardfheidhmíochta, go háirithe le haghaidh soilse treorach."

msgid "To avoid performance issues, it's recommended to:"
msgstr "Chun saincheisteanna feidhmíochta a sheachaint, moltar:"

msgid ""
"Only use a handful of lights with PCSS shadows enabled at a given time. The "
"effect is generally most visible on large, bright lights. Secondary light "
"sources that are more faint usually don't benefit much from using PCSS "
"shadows."
msgstr ""
"Ná húsáid ach dornán soilse le scáthanna PCSS cumasaithe ag am ar leith. De "
"ghnáth bíonn an éifeacht is infheicthe ar shoilse móra geal. De ghnáth ní "
"bhaineann foinsí solais tánaisteacha atá níos caolaí mórán leas as scáthanna "
"PCSS a úsáid."

msgid ""
"Provide a setting for users to disable PCSS shadows. On directional lights, "
"this can be done by setting the DirectionalLight3D's "
"``light_angular_distance`` property to ``0.0`` in a script. On positional "
"lights, this can be done by setting the OmniLight3D or SpotLight3D's "
"``light_size`` property to ``0.0`` in a script."
msgstr ""
"Suíomh a sholáthar d'úsáideoirí scáthanna PCSS a dhíchumasú. Maidir le "
"soilse treorach, is féidir é seo a dhéanamh trí mhaoin "
"`light_angular_distance`` DirectionAllight3D a shocrú go ``0.0`` i script. "
"Maidir le soilse suímh, is féidir é seo a dhéanamh trí mhaoin `light_size`` "
"an OmniLight3D nó Spotlight3D a shocrú go `0.0`` i script."

msgid "Projector filter mode"
msgstr "Modh scagaire teilgeoir"

msgid ""
"The way projectors are rendered also has an impact on performance. The "
"**Rendering > Textures > Light Projectors > Filter** advanced project "
"setting lets you control how projector textures should be filtered. "
"**Nearest/Linear** do not use mipmaps, which makes them faster to render. "
"However, projectors will look grainy at distance. **Nearest/Linear Mipmaps** "
"will look smoother at a distance, but projectors will look blurry when "
"viewed from oblique angles. This can be resolved by using **Nearest/Linear "
"Mipmaps Anisotropic**, which is the highest-quality mode but also the most "
"expensive."
msgstr ""
"Bíonn tionchar freisin ag an mbealach a rindreáiltear teilgeoirí ar "
"fheidhmíocht. Ligeann ardsocrú tionscadail **Rindreáil > Uigeachtaí > "
"Teilgeoirí Solais > Scagaire** duit rialú a dhéanamh ar an gcaoi ar cheart "
"uigeachtaí teilgeoirí a scagadh. **Is gaire/Líneach** ná bain úsáid as "
"mipmaps, rud a fhágann gur tapúla iad le rindreáil. Mar sin féin, féachfaidh "
"teilgeoirí grainy i bhfad. Breathnóidh **Mipmapaí is gaire/Líneacha** i "
"bhfad níos míne, ach beidh cuma doiléir ar theilgeoirí nuair a "
"bhreathnaítear orthu ó uillinneacha fiar. Is féidir é seo a réiteach trí "
"úsáid a bhaint as **Mipmaps Anisotrópacha is gaire/Líneach**, arb é an modh "
"is airde cáilíochta ach an ceann is daoire freisin."

msgid ""
"If your project has a pixel art style, consider setting the filter to one of "
"the **Nearest** values so that projectors use nearest-neighbor filtering. "
"Otherwise, stick to **Linear**."
msgstr ""
"Má tá stíl ealaíne picteilín ag do thionscadal, smaoinigh ar an scagaire a "
"shocrú go ceann de na luacha**is gaire** ionas go n-úsáideann teilgeoirí "
"scagadh comharsa is gaire. Seachas sin, cloí len**Línear**."
